summary: An Ordinance authorizing the Mayor and City Comptroller to issue Local Improvement Bonds for the improvement of Thirty-eighth Avenue from a point 155 feet south of the south, line of East Union Street to the south lien of East Olive Street et al in the City of Seattle, by paving under Ordinance No. 24724, creating Local Improvement District No. 2376 prescribing the rate of interest thereon and authorizing their delivery to the contractor constructing the improvement.
